    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Moment to Savor</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter by Asami Itoh on sportsmanship of US figure skaters Tara Lipinski and Nicole Bobek; expresses disappointment at Michelle Kwan's failure to acknowledge and congratulate Lipinski during post-competition interview with CBS's Jim Nantz (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>How refreshing it was to see Tara Lipinski and her other teammates, including the often maligned Nicole Bobek, enjoy the closing ceremony without any outward indication that their agents had told them to appear. They carried on just like two spirited teen-agers savoring the moment completely unstaged.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>How refreshing it was to see Tara Lipinski and her other teammates, including the often maligned Nicole Bobek, enjoy the closing ceremony without any outward indication that their agents had told them to appear. They carried on just like two spirited teen-agers savoring the moment completely unstaged.</p>
        <p>Maybe Michelle Kwan would have been able to put her disappointment in the proper perspective if she had joined them.</p>
        <p>Although I was disappointed that Kwan did not win the gold, I was more disappointed that Kwan failed to acknowledge and congratulate her teammate during the post-competition interview with CBS's Jim Nantz.</p>
        <p>ASAMI ITOH  Easton, Conn.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
